dcterms:creator: B. van Dongen
dcterms:description: This dataset includes the loan application process execution history for a Dutch banking institution. Every instance in this log documents the events surrounding a certain loan application. Labellings were established for classification reasons depending upon the outcome of a case, i.e., whether the application is approved, denied, or cancelled.
dcterms:title: BPIC2012

dcterms:creator: B. van Dongen
dcterms:description: This dataset consists of event logs from 5 different municipalities in the Netherlands regarding a building permit application process. Each municipality's data is treated as a separate event log with a single labelling function applied to each one.
dcterms:title: BPIC2015

dcterms:creator: B. van Dongen
dcterms:description: This event log originates from the same financial institution as the BPIC2012 dataset. The data collection has been improved, resulting in a richer and cleaner dataset that records execution traces of a loan application process.
dcterms:title: BPIC2017

dcterms:creator: F. Mannhardt

dcterms:title: Sepsis

dcterms:description: This event log records execution traces of a public contract auction in Italy and whether any recourses have been registered. It involves the Public Administration of a region requiring a service to be done and holding a public contest where private contractors can bid.
